\[§ XXXVIII. The Sun is consecrated to Osiris, and the lion is
worshipped, and temples are ornamented with figures of this animal,
because the Nile rises when the sun is in the constellation of the Lion.
Horus, the offspring of Osiris, the Nile, and Isis, the Earth, was born
in the marshes of Buto, because the vapour of damp land destroys
drought. Nephthys, or Teleute, represents the extreme limits of the
country and the sea-shore, that is, barren land. Osiris (i.e., the Nile)
overflowed this barren land, and Anubis <span
id="fr_340"></span>[2](leg62.htm#fn_338.md) was the result. <span
id="fr_341"></span>[3](leg62.htm#fn_339.md)\]

